This paper deals with the optimal control of battery storage systems for frequency control services, which involves the use of control algorithms and optimization techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a data-driven approach and a detailed battery model, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the techno-economic analysis of battery storage systems, which could place it in the cs.ET (Economics and Computation) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper deals with the degradation of batteries, which could place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category, as this is a common issue in distributed systems. Finally, the paper deals with the use of battery storage systems in the context of the energy sector, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.EE (Electrical Engineering) sub-category.
